## Goal

Deploy encrypted archive to Cloudflare Pages as an alternative to GitHub Pages.

## Why Cloudflare Pages?

- **Native COOP/COEP headers**: Better cross-origin isolation support
- **No 100MB file limit**: Handles larger archives
- **Private repos free**: No paid plan required
- **Edge network**: Fast global CDN

## Implementation

### Prerequisites Check

```rust
pub fn check_wrangler_prerequisites() -> Prerequisites {
    Prerequisites {
        wrangler_cli: check_wrangler_version(),
        wrangler_authenticated: check_wrangler_auth(),
    }
}

fn check_wrangler_version() -> Option<String> {
    std::process::Command::new("wrangler")
        .arg("--version")
        .output()
        .ok()
        .and_then(|o| String::from_utf8(o.stdout).ok())
}

fn check_wrangler_auth() -> bool {
    std::process::Command::new("wrangler")
        .args(["whoami"])
        .status()
        .map(|s| s.success())
        .unwrap_or(false)
}
```

### Deployment Flow

```rust
pub async fn deploy_to_cloudflare(
    site_dir: &Path,
    project_name: &str,
    config: &CloudflareConfig,
) -> Result<DeploymentResult, DeployError> {
    // 1. Create project if needed
    if !project_exists(project_name).await? {
        create_project(project_name).await?;
    }

    // 2. Deploy using wrangler
    let output = std::process::Command::new("wrangler")
        .args(["pages", "deploy", site_dir.to_str().unwrap()])
        .arg("--project-name")
        .arg(project_name)
        .output()?;

    if !output.status.success() {
        return Err(DeployError::WranglerFailed(
            String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stderr).to_string()
        ));
    }

    // 3. Parse deployment URL from output
    let url = parse_deployment_url(&output.stdout)?;

    Ok(DeploymentResult {
        url,
        project_name: project_name.to_string(),
        deployed_at: Utc::now(),
    })
}
```

### Custom Headers (_headers file)

Cloudflare Pages supports custom headers via `_headers` file:

```rust
pub fn generate_cloudflare_headers(site_dir: &Path) -> Result<()> {
    let headers = r#"/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow
"#;

    std::fs::write(site_dir.join("_headers"), headers)?;
    Ok(())
}
```

### wrangler.toml Configuration

```rust
pub fn generate_wrangler_config(project_name: &str) -> String {
    format!(r#"
name = "{}"
pages_build_output_dir = "site"

[build]
command = ""

[[headers]]
for = "/*"
[headers.values]
Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy = "same-origin"
Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy = "require-corp"
"#, project_name)
}
```

