 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-lr2","title":"P5.7 cass sources remove command","description":"# P5.7 cass sources remove command

## Overview
Implement command to remove a configured source and optionally clean up
its synced data.

## Implementation Details

### CLI Definition
```rust
#[derive(Parser)]
pub enum SourcesCommand {
    /// Remove a configured source
    Remove {
        /// Name of source to remove
        name: String,

        /// Also delete synced session data
        #[arg(long)]
        purge: bool,

        /// Skip confirmation prompt
        #[arg(long, short = 'y')]
        yes: bool,
    },
    // ...
}
```

### Implementation
```rust
async fn cmd_sources_remove(args: &RemoveArgs) -> Result<(), CliError> {
    let mut config = SourcesConfig::load()?;

    // Find source
    let idx = config.sources.iter()
        .position(|s| s.name == args.name)
        .ok_or_else(|| CliError::SourceNotFound(args.name.clone()))?;

    // Confirm
    if !args.yes {
        let msg = if args.purge {
            format!(
                "Remove source '{}' and delete all synced data? This cannot be undone.",
                args.name
            )
        } else {
            format!(
                "Remove source '{}' from configuration? Synced data will be preserved.",
                args.name
            )
        };

        if !confirm(&msg)? {
            println!("Cancelled.");
            return Ok(());
        }
    }

    // Remove from config
    config.sources.remove(idx);
    config.save()?;
    println!("Removed '{}' from configuration.", args.name);

    // Optionally purge data
    if args.purge {
        let data_dir = dirs::data_local_dir()?.join("cass/remotes").join(&args.name);
        if data_dir.exists() {
            std::fs::remove_dir_all(&data_dir)?;
            println!("Deleted synced data at {:?}", data_dir);

            // Also remove from index
            remove_source_from_index(&args.name).await?;
            println!("Removed from search index.");
        }
    }

    Ok(())
}
```

## Dependencies
- Requires P5.1 (config types)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Source removed from config file
- [ ] Confirmation prompt unless -y
- [ ] `--purge` deletes synced data and index entries
- [ ] Helpful error if source not found","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-16T01:08:03.718383-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-16T14:36:10.171177-05:00","closed_at":"2025-12-16T14:36:10.171177-05:00","close_reason":"Implemented sources remove command with confirmation prompt, --purge option for data cleanup, and helpful error messages","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-lr2","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-luj","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-12-16T01:09:23.79805-05:00","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}"}]}
